What is the representative Münchhausen syndrome that appeared in The Politician of Netflix?
The symptoms are that parents and parents false that healthy children are sick.
The Politician is broadcast today on Netflix.
The drama is about Patton Hobart, the president of the United States, but the first step is to become the student council president of his high school.
The film was produced by American Horror Story and Gree creator Ryan Murphy, starring Gwinnes Partlow, Ben Pratt, and Lucy Bointon.
This is a mental illness where parents behave as if they were physically or mentally ill, even though the person under the protection is not really sick.
There are many different types of conditions, including Münchhausen syndrome, which is falsely believed to be a disease of himself.
However, the surrogate Münchhausen syndrome is clearly false that others under their protection are ill.
It is also known as FII or FII, a type of child abuse.
It is a rare symptom, but usually parents exaggerate or cause symptoms, as if a child is sick.
What are the signs of Münchhausen syndrome?
The symptoms of the disease vary in case-by-case, but NHS points out the following cautions.
The child is healthy, but if he is sick, he tries to persuade the medical practitioner.
It can be described as exaggerated or false.
The test results are fabricated to make the child feel sick, such as by mixing glucose into the urine sample and showing it to be diabetes.
Excessive medications and other drugs cause symptoms of disease.
How general is Muhnhausen syndrome?
Since many cases have not been reported, it is difficult to know how widespread this syndrome is.
A study published in 2000 estimated that there were 89 cases of 100,000 people in two years.
what should we do if we suspect child damage?
Contact local social welfare organizations or call NSPCC Child Protection Helpline 0808 800 5000.
