Three-tier, prefectural high vows to remove gender column Consideration for sexual minorities: Hokkaido Shimbun
It was found on 28th that the Mie Prefectural Board of Education decided to remove the gender column of the prefectural high school entrance application for consideration of sexual minorities such as transgenders whose mind and body do not match.
The Board of Education of the prefecture approved the entrance examination for applicants in FY18 by selecting gender fields and writing them without filling them, but from FY20 the items themselves were eliminated.
For the classification of classes and the grouping of physical education, we use research papers created by junior high school.
However, in order to be able to freely fill in the questionnaire according to the circumstances of the student, the gender field that was selected is described.
According to the Board of Education, the gender column for the public high vows has been removed from Osaka Prefecture and Fukuoka Prefecture since FY19, and Hokkaido and Kanagawa Prefecture have decided to remove them from FY20.
