i agree to pay 30 million dollars for epipen settlement
The company agreed to pay $30 million in settlement for the failure of investors to disclose information about the U.S. Department of Justice's investigation on the presence of overclaims on epipenes against Medicades.
On Friday, the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) announced that it had classified epipen as "generic" in the Medicaid drug rebate program.
This led to the discovery that payments from pharmaceutical companies to governments were extremely low compared to those classified as "brands."
The company announced in July that it had reached a fundamental agreement with the SEC on this matter.
The statement issued on Friday did not affirm or deny the SEC's claims.
Stepping the accelerator pedal will eliminate accidents!
Yahoo! News
you can buy it at a reasonable price.
A traffic accident caused by driver error.
In particular, accidents caused by brake and accelerator mistakes by elderly drivers are on an increasing trend.
In particular, when it comes to sudden departure, it becomes a panic, and sometimes the accelerator is still stepping on the brake pedal.
There are new vehicles equipped with safety driver support functions that cover such errors, but there are also rearing devices that can be attached to unattended vehicles.
After-sales parts manufacturers are developing and selling rapid start prevention and prevention systems.
I would like to introduce what characteristics each has.
The pedal interval between the accelerator and the brake is narrow, and the pedal is stepped at the same time.
[e-ACCEL ALARM] "e-ACCEL ALARM" developed by Pivot is to inform pedal mistakes from a new perspective.
It is to avoid pedal mistakes with "an alarm."
The system generates "an alarm sound" when you step on the accelerator pedal by mistake of stepping on the brake when stopping or driving at low speed.
It is to react to the sound and encourage the accelerator to return, and to avoid rapid acceleration by quickly recognizing the mistake of stepping.
It is difficult to understand the change in engine sound due to the mistake of stepping on the accelerator, and it is effective for elderly drivers who can hear it.
It is attached to the OBDII connector and the main body is attached with double-sided tape.
The price is 9800 yen (excluding tax) and it is affordable, and it is also attractive that you need to set up.
[Ashimo Watching-kun] The World Wing was launched in mid-September by Ashimo Watching-kun, an accelerator brake prevention device.
It can also be used when retreating (back) without moving forward.
When the accelerator pedal is suddenly stepped in during the advance and retreat from the stop (and less than 10Km/h), the vehicle's speed signal and brake signal are detected and the accelerator opening is suppressed electrically.
When you accidentally step on the accelerator pedal, do not tell the signal from the accelerator, and control the sudden start by instantly turning it into a creep driving state (the state where the brake is removed in the D range).
It is also equipped with a function to detect the speed of approximately 5Km/h or more at the back of the vehicle and force the vehicle to be cleaned.
Installation is possible only with capraon and simple wiring processing.
The price is 37,000 yen (excluding tax).
