Walter is charged with supplying the drug to Cameron Petitt, another person who sold the drug to Miller.
According to a court record released on Tuesday, Petitt was getting drugs from Walter throughout August.
Ryan Levis, arrested earlier this week in Lake Habas City, Arizona, is charged with delivering drugs to Petit as Walter's "deliver."
All three are not directly charged with the death of Mr. Miller, and there is still a defense against each case.
Walter, currently in custody, was placed under probation for a drug case in 2005, and was sentenced to five months in prison for violating his compliance.
The first public prosecutor in charge of the case, reported by Celebrity Site TMZ on Thursday, called for Walter to be detained until the trial began due to the high likelihood of escape.
There was no immediate response to the answering machine.
Petitt was indicted by the federal court on September 4, but the defense counsel refused to comment.
