Aso, an express train of JNR, is a temporary train from Hiroshima to Kumamoto, a 10-hour trip | Shizuoka Shimbun at Ess
To wait for departure at JR Hiroshima Station, a temporary train inspired by the JNR express "Aso" = 28 days
People who enjoy a special train trip inspired by the express train "Aso" of the JNR era = 28
A temporary train was operated between Hiroshima and Kumamoto on the 28th.
In the morning of the same day, about 240 people, including railway fans, boarded a blue 12-car train from Hiroshima Station to Kumamoto Station.
Aso was a night train that connected Kumamoto and Tokyo between 1950 and 1980.
The tour was limited to one round trip (two days), and as part of the "Kumamoto Destination Campaign" by JR companies, the tour was organized by Japanese travelers.
The train consists of seven cars, including passenger cars and locomotives, and runs on the Sanyo, Chikuho and Kagoshima lines.
A special headmark was drawn on Mt. Aso.
his brother's life imprisonment for the honor murder of kandir barochi, a Pakistani social media star.
Candir Barochi, who gained fame in photos posted on social media, was strangled in July 2016.
One of Pakistan's most popular social media outlets, Candir Barochi's older brother, was convicted of murdering his sister on Friday, and sentenced to life imprisonment for the most popular "honorary murder" in Pakistan.
Baroch was strangled in July 2016 when he was famous for his selfie photography - which is not as big as Western standards, but was provocative in Pakistan, which is very strong in women's contempt.
His brother, Muhammad, was arrested.
His brother said in a press conference a few days later that he killed his sister, of course, that his sister's actions were "unforgivable," and that he did not regret what he did.
Mr. Sardar Memood, a lawyer, told AFP that the court of the eastern city of Murtan was convicted and sentenced to life in a waiting sentence.
"Inshirar will be innocent in the Supreme Court," he said.
Prior to this, Barochi's mother, Anwar Mai, told AFP that she wanted her son to be innocent.
"There is no sin for my son.
My daughter and my son."
Barochi's murder has become a major news all over the world, and as a result of neglecting the rules of father-right society, the voices of victims, most women, who seek action against the spread of so-called "honorary murders."
Women have been burned, killed, stabbed or strangled by crimes such as choosing their own marriage partner - in Barochi's case, appraising their sexuality and humiliating their family.
The killing is usually done by close relatives.
After that, Pakistan's Kisas and Deya laws allow perpetrators to be pardoned by relatives of the victim.
Three months after Barochi's murder, Congress passed a new bill requiring life imprisonment for honorary murder.
However, it is up to the judge's discretion to determine whether murder is an honorable crime, and the killer can theoretically claim a different motive and may be pardoned.
In Baroch's case, his parents initially insisted not give his son a pardon.
However, his parents changed their minds and asked him to forgive him.
Due to international hatred of killing, the Pakistani government took unprecedented steps to declare the country as a successor with their parents, but the lawsuit continued.
Barochi's famous actions include offering a strip show to the Pakistan Cricket team and wearing a bright red dress with a wide chest on Valentine's Day.
Although criticized and threatened, it was recognized by many people, including young people, that the expression of oneself as an existence such as Kim Kardashian has opened up a new heaven and earth in a country considered to be a bold and political activity to improve the status of women.
The origins of "honorary" murder are ethnic social norms, which still remain widely in South Asia, particularly affecting women's behavior, although men may be victims.
To donate 1,600 sheets and storage boxes to the disaster-affected areas of Yamagata Prefecture | Yamagata Shimbun
A cold-proof seat box set up in the former Nenjuseki Naka Ground, the first evacuation site in the Ingugaseki district of Tsuruoka City.
Yamagata Shimbun will donate 1,600 sheets of cold and heat-resistant aluminum sheet for refugees and 5 outdoor storage boxes (equivalent to approximately 1 million yen) to the four autonomous associations in the Atami area of Tsuruoka City, which were affected by the June earthquake that struck off the coast of Honshu Island.
In order to prepare for the tsunami, they will be placed in the "first evacuation site" located in each coastal area.
The ceremony will be held next month at the "Old Nenjuseki Naka Ground," the first evacuation site in the Ingukenoseki area.
Due to the damage caused by the earthquake that occurred in Tsuruoka City, which has concluded a partnership agreement, a cold-proof sheet is presented to the local council of the Atami region closest to the epicenter.
It is the home of the 400-piece Rock River (500 storage boxes, two storage boxes) and the 300-piece, one storage box.
When the earthquake struck off the coast of Japan, many of the residents of the coast of Japan were evacuated due to the tsunami.
He escaped to the first evacuation site in Tsuruoka City, which was located on the hill of each village.
Although there were no large tsunamis, most of the refugees returned home without moving to a second evacuation site with facilities and facilities that could be accommodated, many of the first evacuation sites were outdoors, and there were voices calling for cold.
As a precautionary measure to prepare for similar disasters, measures for severe cold periods and wind and rain were one of the challenges.
Seats that can cover the whole body during evacuation and relieve cold and wind rain.
it also has a heat shield function in the flaming world.
The seat is about 1.3 meters x 2.1 meters, and when folded, it becomes a pocket size of 9 centimeters x 12 centimeters.
The four-layer structure is used to cover the body by using the gold and silver fronts and backs to cover the body.
A metal box is installed at the first evacuation site located outdoors.
