The Sonnet Media Networks (SMN) began advertising for header binding by "Prebid.js" in LFP.
LFP is a service that enables customers to purchase and plan their own ad frame according to their requests.
This service provides an effective advertising framework through DSP through collaboration with media companies.
Header biding is a system in which multiple bidders (advertisers) compete in fair bidding to deliver high-priced ads to media operated by media companies preferentially.
As a solution that is transparent for media companies and is expected to improve profitability, it is being introduced mainly by major media.
In the past, SSP has been providing advertising frames through SSP.
In recent years, in order to respond to requests from advertisers that "we want to deliver to certain ad frames that have high affinity with individual commercial materials and brand images," LFP started in December last year, in collaboration with media companies, to directly purchase advertising frames to meet the needs of advertisers.
This time, the introduction of LFP will be expanded by supporting header binding.
As a benefit for advertisers, LFP header binding allows them to participate in bidding directly for header binding target ad frames, which is expected to improve their advertising delivery opportunities.
In addition, because the target media company is limited, the advertisement frame of each product and the delivery destination according to the brand image is secured, preventing brand value damage.
One of the advantages of media companies is that the solution to manage the code of each bidder company, called the " wrapper solution," which LFP promotes collaboration, enables initiatives that meet the expectations of the introduction of media companies.
