China needs strong leadership, otherwise collapse - policy documents
Prior to the 70th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China, the Chinese government stated in a policy document published on Friday.
In the White Paper, the State Council of China said that the success of the Communist Party's administration 70 years ago was due to the leadership of the party.
China is vast, and domestic affairs are complicated, but there are few political problems.
Without a unified and powerful leadership, China will face divisions and collapses, and will be a catastrophe for the world."
The Chinese authorities have long justified addressing problems in a rigid manner, such as the repression of the democratic movement in Beijing in 1989 as necessary for national stability.
President Xi Jinping, who is the leading figure in the world's second largest economic power commemorative ceremony, held on Tuesday, has strengthened the party's control since he took power in late 2012 and has tightened the human resistance against the party.
Xi has also overseen military modernization programs threatening the area.
The policy document states that China does not intend to export the development model of its own country, nor does it intend to incorporate models of other countries, and that it merely seeks peace rather than supremacy.
Among the genes of Chinese people, there is no invasion or world control of other people.
In modern times, China was bullied by the powerful, and war and chaos left a deep scar with that pain; China would never take the pain he experienced to others.
China is facing difficult issues such as economic stagnation and anti-government movements in China's Hong Kong.
The White Paper states that China will never "abandon" its core interests, nor allow its security and sovereignty to be undermined.
"The threat of trade wars and rising tariffs do not lead to any problem-solving," White Paper states.
China is a mature economic nation with complete industrial systems, complete industrial chains, wide market space and momentum of strong economic development.
"It will never weaken in the trade war," White said.
I am convinced that China has the power to face difficulties, turn crisis into opportunities and open a new world.
He added that the United States should take the development of China calmly, as China has no idea of countering the United States and does not want to replace the United States.
The United States cannot control China, and it is less likely that China will stop its development.
The United States would not maintain its strength if it would suppress, suppress, and move domestic contradictions abroad.
