The 300-year history of kumi odori / educational promotion project | Miyako Mainichi Shimbun Website - The latest news on Miyakojima is packed!
Workshops in Kagamihara
Workshop on the role and effect of five musical instruments played by kumi odori (a group dance) = 26th, Kagamihara Junior High School
A group dance workshop (hosted by the Prefectural Board of Education and Education Agency) was held at Kagamihara Junior High School on June 26.
All students attended and learned about the 300-year history and birth of kumi odori, as well as the acoustic effects and utilization of the instruments played.
In the workshop, members of the OB Group, Department of Ryukyu Performing Arts, Prefectural University of Arts, introduced the role of each instrument in kumidori while playing sanshin, koto, taiko, kokyu and flute.
The moderator was Mr. Kata Kawaman, a member of the OB association from Miyakojima City and introduced the charm of kumi odori.
In this workshop, I learned about the three components of kumidori (music, chanting, Ryukyu dance) and how five kinds of instruments are expressed in dance.
As for the Sanshin, it was explained that it was an element of the movement and emotional expression of the characters along with the song, and that Kokyu was pulling up the song and the melody of the Sanshin while playing.
In the second half, the students actually touched the instrument and experienced the sound of it, and felt the charm of the instrument.
This initiative was implemented with the aim of becoming familiar with Ryukyu classical music through musical instruments, and to have many students interested in kumi odori, this is the first time in Miyako.
