More than 100 honey bees were collected from only two nest boxes.
Why did Bentley make bees on the site of a factory where cars were assembled?
I want to taste this!
Here are 11 honeys produced by Bentley.
Peter Bosch, executive director of Bentley's manufacturing department, commented as follows.
"In order to contribute to the conservation of biodiversity in the region, we established a nest box for the first time in the vast grounds of the Crew Plant at the beginning of this year.
The beekeepers watched the bees from the wildflowers planted on the site and the surrounding mountains as they were gathering honey from various flowers.
It turns out that this place is suitable for beekeeping, and it is wonderful to have such a harvest in the first year.
Bentley is engaged in a wide range of activities through its Crew Plant and our business to become the top sustainable luxury car manufacturer, and is part of this.
Staff are actively cooperating.
