9.2% of Taiwanese high school students "experienced" percentage increase that does not contraception = Health Authorities Survey (Central Company Focus Taiwan) - Yahoo! News
(Taipei 27) National Health Department (Ministry of Health) National Health Department (Ministry of Health) released a survey on sexual intercourse and other experiences of high school students in Taiwan on September 26.
According to this, 9.2% of students answered that they had experience.
Of these, about one in five did not have contraception.
The survey was conducted in 2017 for students enrolled in high schools, specialized high schools and technical colleges.
Compared to the previous survey, the percentage of students with sexual intercourse decreased slightly from 11.1% in the previous survey.
On the other hand, 22.6% of men and women aged 15 to 17 answered that they did not contraception due to the latest sexual activity, exceeding 19.2% in the previous year.
The breakdown is 28.8% of males (22.6%) and 12.2% of females (14.5 percent).
The station pointed out that modern youths have more opportunities to get information on the Internet, and their thinking is likely to be biased by misinformation.
He calls for correct knowledge as not only pregnancy but also increased risk of infection.
