The JR Omura Line, which saw operation due to damage from the track due to Typhoon No. 17, resumed operation from the start of the 27th morning.
The JR Omura Line, the Sasebo Line, and the Nagasaki Main Line started on the morning of the 27th and returned to normal operation.
The JR Omura Line is the intermediate point between Kawabata Station and Heki Station, and the protective shore of the side of the tracks collapsed due to the typhoon, and the foundations flowed.
In addition, the number of JR trains in Nagasaki Prefecture decreased and the timetables continued to deteriorate.
According to the JR Kyushu Nagasaki Branch, the restoration work was completed on the 26th, and after running the test drive in the early morning of the 27th, the operation resumed.
