Royal Caribbean cruise ship Explorer of the Seas, renovated for £89 million
The Explorer of the Seas, operated by Royal Caribbean International, will sail in a new outfit this summer.
This cruise ship, which cost $110 million (£8.9 million), is a place where you can enjoy the delicious cuisine of the world and enjoy the whole family.
This summer, Explorer stops at the highest ports in Italy and Greece, where passengers can enjoy the feeling of Mediterranean Europe.
After an adventure on land is over, you will be able to experience a memorable experience at sea.
After renovations of $110 million (equivalent to £89 million), the cruise ship was transformed into a perfect family trip for anyone to enjoy.
With excellent technology, passengers can enjoy surfing on deck with high-performance surf simulators, and enjoy a wonderful climate in an outdoor cinema while watching family favourite shows.
However, the most innovative feature is the addition of a virtual balcony, allowing passengers to enjoy ocean views from their rooms.
For those who like water, there is a swimming pool deck that is re-imagined to be enjoyed like a water park in the Caribbean Resort style.
The poolside is home to island-style hammocks and long chairs, ideal for sunbathing, and two modern water slides for those who want to enjoy thrills on board.
This cruise ship is attractive to all ages and offers plenty of activities to spend time at the port.
Kids Adventure Oceans for children give young children a chance to make good memories, and a teens-only pool has a corner for games and music for 12 and over.
If this is not enough, the whole family will be able to compete against the dark laser tag game in Studio B, which also serves as an ice skating rink.
The diversified on-board restaurant offers guests the opportunity to enjoy cuisine all over the world while sailing through the Mediterranean.
At the restaurant Ismi, you can enjoy the latest Asian cuisine, and at the traditional and modern Italian restaurant Giovanni's Italian Kitchen, you can enjoy the finest cuisine in a casual atmosphere.
Other restaurants include Chops Grill American Steakhouse, Boleros Latin Bar, Schuner Bar, and Johnny Rockets Express.
Cruise tours are available for 7 nights and 9 nights, with plans to leave Rome in May 2020.
Explorer is the second European ship of the Royal Caribbean, following the recently renovated Allure of the Sea.
The refurbishment cost $165 million, and the 58-day Aleures offered 300 dollars worth of bonus benefits for early bookings.
According to the cruise company, " Explorer of the Sea is the fourth Voyager class fully renovated as part of the modernization of the Royal Amplifier."
The program, which invested more than $1 billion in ten vessels over four years, provides a wide range of thrill-filled adventures, including attractions that can only be experienced here, experiential meals and nightlife.
