I had a boyfriend all the time, but due to his work, I had a long distance romance ....
I was told to marry someday, but I couldn't see the goal.
In such a situation, how can we connect the situation to marriage by side?
Editorial I of Nikkei Doors asked Professor Tomoyoshi Morikawa to give a lecture on "love studies" at Waseda University.
Prof. Morikawa's advice, which was derived from detailed data analysis, is required to read.
what's this?
I am worried whether I should continue dating my boyfriend during a long distance romance.
I want to continue living in Kansai where I work and my family home, but his place of work is Tokyo.
Since it is a trading company, it is possible to transfer overseas.
It is said that we will marry in the future, but we cannot see the goal at all.
What should I do?
(23 years old, manufacturer, office)
The couple who got married from long distance love is a minority.
Nikkei doors Editorial Department (--) C is in a long-distance relationship with her boyfriend for one and a half years.
There is also the word "to be tested at a distance and the two become stronger."Is long distance love going well in the first place?
Prof. Tomoyoshi Morikawa (hereinafter referred to as Morikawa) Speaking of distance love, DeNA Travel's questionnaire survey (held in August 2017, 1147 people answered) is famous, but according to the data, only 16% of couples from distance love to marriage are known.
Since love is done with five senses, the relationship is deepened by seeing the partner (visual), listening to the voice (heart), connecting the hand (touch), smelling (olfactory), kissing (taste).
However, in the case of long distance love, there are many cases where you can hear the voice by phone.
It may be difficult to keep up with hearing alone.
There is also a cost problem.
If you go to the other person's house, you will be burdened with time and effort to move to the transportation cost, and even though it is a holiday to heal the tiredness of work, your body is a kata.
I feel refreshed when I return home.
Does that mean you have to break up when you're far away?
Morikawa If you are a couple who can endure even if you don't meet frequently, or a couple that has a certain period of time in advance, I think it will work.
You'll be engaged a year later, or you'll come back from your transfer two years later.
It may be difficult if you do not see a future landing point.
