The Hokkaido Board of Education announced on September 26, 2019, that it would select students for Hokkaido Prefectural High School in 2020.
It is important to note that students who take transgender exams do not match their mind and body, and to abolish the gender column from the format of the application form.
Selection schedule
The selection of applicants for Doritsu High School has been compiled into one book, including the selection schedule, the number of applicants, application qualification, application procedure, application change, academic examination, acceptance announcement, etc.
It includes the selection of general admissions, the selection of recommended applicants, the selection of applicants for Doritsu High School which implements integrated middle and high school education, and selection of applicants for applications from outside Hokkaido.
Until the 2019 entrance examination, there was a gender column in the application form, but considering the necessity of appropriate consideration for the diversity of sexual orientation and gender identity of individuals, the selection of applicants for the 2020 entrance examination will cut the "sex" column from the format of the application form.
The school offers five courses in Japanese, mathematics, society, science and English.
English listening tests are included in the English test time.
The examination time for each subject is 50 minutes.
The time required for the answer is 45 minutes, and the time required to pay attention to the examiner and to distribute the problem paper is set for 5 minutes immediately after the examination.
The school has 60 courses.
The deadline for admission to Hokkaido Prefectural High School in 2020 is at noon on January 21-24, 2020, when applications for general selection are accepted, from January 29 to February 4, 4:00 p.m., on March 4, at 10:00 p.m. on March 17, and on March 23-24 at 4:30 p.m. on March 27.
Applications will be accepted at noon on January 21-24, 2020, interviews will be held at noon on February 13, and interviews will be notified on February 20.
