No. 8 Konotori, an unmanned supply vehicle that arrived at the International Space Station.
The robot arm of the station is growing from the bottom left (NASA provided).
The International Space Station (ISS) successfully caught Konotori No. 8 and applauded JAXA officials on July 28.
On the night of the 28th, the unmanned replenishment machine Konotori 8 (JAXA) of the Japan Aerospace Exploration Agency (JAXA), carrying supplies to the International Space Station (ISS), which is about 400 kilometers altitude, arrived near the station, and the astronauts during their stay operated the robotic arm and caught it.
